# ==========================================================================
# ACT yeast self-reproduction
#
# Applied constructor-theory case:
# A yeast starter culture is modeled as a self-reproducer.
# - the genome is the replicator
# - the cell machinery is the vehicle
# - a nutrient bath supplies raw materials
# - a fermenter provides a selection environment
#
# This encodes Marletto's constructor-theoretic logic:
# accurate replication under no-design laws requires digital information and
# a replicator-plus-vehicle architecture.
# ==========================================================================

@prefix : <http://example.org/act/yeast/> .
@prefix log: <http://www.w3.org/2000/10/swap/log#> .

:world :obeys :NoDesignLaws .

:dnaRegister a :DigitalInformationMedium .

:starterGenome a :Replicator ;
  :accuracy :High ;
  :variant :RespireFast ;
  :storedIn :dnaRegister .

:starterVehicle a :Vehicle ;
  :function :Metabolism ;
  :function :CopyingSupport .

:starterCell a :Cell ;
  :hasReplicator :starterGenome ;
  :hasVehicle :starterVehicle .

:nutrientBath a :RawMaterialSupply .

:mutationSource a :VariationSource .

:fermenter a :SelectionEnvironment ;
  :favours :RespireFast .

# ---------------------------
# Constructor-theoretic rules
# ---------------------------

{ :world :obeys :NoDesignLaws .
  :dnaRegister a :DigitalInformationMedium . }
=>
{ :ReplicationUnderNoDesignLaws a :PossibleTask . } .

{ :starterGenome a :Replicator .
  :starterGenome :storedIn :dnaRegister .
  :ReplicationUnderNoDesignLaws a :PossibleTask . }
=>
{ :GenomeCopying a :PossibleTask . } .

{ :starterGenome :accuracy :High .
  :starterCell :hasReplicator :starterGenome .
  :starterCell :hasVehicle :starterVehicle .
  :starterVehicle a :Vehicle . }
=>
{ :AccurateReplicationArchitecture a :PossibleTask . } .

{ :GenomeCopying a :PossibleTask .
  :AccurateReplicationArchitecture a :PossibleTask .
  :nutrientBath a :RawMaterialSupply . }
=>
{ :starterCell a :SelfReproducer . } .

{ :starterCell a :SelfReproducer . }
=>
{ :SelfReproduction a :PossibleTask . } .

{ :starterGenome a :Replicator .
  :mutationSource a :VariationSource . }
=>
{ :HeritableVariation a :PossibleTask . } .

{ :SelfReproduction a :PossibleTask .
  :HeritableVariation a :PossibleTask .
  :fermenter a :SelectionEnvironment . }
=>
{ :NaturalSelection a :PossibleTask . } .

{ :NaturalSelection a :PossibleTask .
  :starterGenome :variant ?V .
  :fermenter :favours ?V . }
=>
{ :starterGenome :selectedIn :fermenter . } .

# ------
# Checks
# ------

{ :world :obeys :NoDesignLaws . }
=> { :case :checkC1 :Passed . } .

{ :dnaRegister a :DigitalInformationMedium . }
=> { :case :checkC2 :Passed . } .

{ :starterGenome a :Replicator . }
=> { :case :checkC3 :Passed . } .

{ :starterVehicle a :Vehicle . }
=> { :case :checkC4 :Passed . } .

{ :AccurateReplicationArchitecture a :PossibleTask . }
=> { :case :checkC5 :Passed . } .

{ :GenomeCopying a :PossibleTask . }
=> { :case :checkC6 :Passed . } .

{ :starterCell a :SelfReproducer . }
=> { :case :checkC7 :Passed . } .

{ :HeritableVariation a :PossibleTask . }
=> { :case :checkC8 :Passed . } .

{ :NaturalSelection a :PossibleTask . }
=> { :case :checkC9 :Passed . } .

{ :starterGenome :selectedIn :fermenter . }
=> { :case :checkC10 :Passed . } .

# ------
# Output
# ------

{ :case :checkC1 :Passed .
  :case :checkC2 :Passed .
  :case :checkC3 :Passed .
  :case :checkC4 :Passed .
  :case :checkC5 :Passed .
  :case :checkC6 :Passed .
  :case :checkC7 :Passed .
  :case :checkC8 :Passed .
  :case :checkC9 :Passed .
  :case :checkC10 :Passed . }
=>
{
  :out log:outputString """ACT yeast self-reproduction

Answer
YES.
This yeast starter culture is a viable applied constructor-theory case of accurate self-reproduction under no-design laws.

Reason Why
The genome is treated as a replicator storing digital information, while the cell machinery is treated as the vehicle that enables metabolism and copying support. Under no-design laws, digital information makes genome copying possible. Because the replicator is accurate and paired with a vehicle, the whole cell qualifies as a self-reproducer. With a variation source and a selection environment, natural selection also becomes possible.

Check
C1  OK - no-design laws are assumed
C2  OK - digital information is physically instantiated
C3  OK - a replicator is present
C4  OK - a vehicle is present
C5  OK - accurate replication is supported by a replicator-plus-vehicle architecture
C6  OK - genome copying is possible
C7  OK - the starter cell qualifies as a self-reproducer
C8  OK - heritable variation is possible
C9  OK - natural selection is possible
C10 OK - the fitter variant is selected in the fermenter
""" .
} .
